Identify {= author_publication =}+ publications as patents on flexible tensile-member actuated robotic manipulators (cable, tendon, fiber, rope, wire, etc.) for humanoid (or adjacent) robotic hands (again, or adjacent, e.g. fingers, wrists, forearms, arms, appendages, grippers, ...) by providing a suitable source (i.e. {= url =}+ URLs per publication) covering the patent publication (original invention whitepaper with the patent mentioned, the patent application, grant-issuing page, aggregated patent-family record — when containing appropriate particular-patent details like bibliography / technical text — or similar) and reporting a source-exposed id number (or equivalent; normally a country-prefix + kind-code such as `US...B2`) plus a date (e.g. for grant pages that could be the grant issuing date). A publication is identified by its (human-readable) title and the author / assignee / applicant name (proper name or institution name when more applicable).

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the claimed publication title.
- The page must clearly identify the claimed author name (and, obviously, establish said author as author for the specific publication in question).
- The page should exhibit evidence characterizing the invention as a humanoid robotic hand (or adjacent).
- The page should describe a flexible tensile-member as part of the invention's actuation / force-transmission path.
- The page must expose a clear id number (or equivalent).
- The page must expose a clear anchor date.
